<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
When I cast globe of light with my mage, I can not see all the area around me before I take a step. Note that this happens only in large areas (empty arena levels, or in melkor god quest for instance) <p>
Bandobras: Me too. I fact, some of the area is lighted, but after a step 1 or 2 more fields in each direction are lighted. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./ErisDiscordia">ErisDiscordia</a>: I ran into this on the Eru quest. Like Bandobras said. Note that this bug is not new to 2.3; it's in 2.2.27 as well. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./JulesBean">JulesBean</a>: Light area does two possible things: if you are in a 'room', then it lights the whole room. If you are not in a room (e.g. arena levels, or in the town at night, etc.) then it lights a certain radius. I think I've noticed that in the second case, the area initially lit is just your light radius, but then a step later more is shown. 
</p>
